This paper discusses the representation of machine-readable dictionaries, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval, making it likely to belong to the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and digital libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the use of markup languages and guidelines for encoding suggest a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI).
